Now first of all, now we are going to shift

00:02:35.480 --> 00:02:39.415
the settings and sizes for our text and everything.

00:02:39.415 --> 00:02:41.940
This is our text.

00:02:41.940 --> 00:02:47.995
First we are going to use 20 pixels because 20 pixels is our baseline size.

00:02:47.995 --> 00:02:52.235
Let's go to 20 pixels and line height was 1.6,

00:02:52.235 --> 00:02:55.670
so it is equal to 32 points.

00:02:55.670 --> 00:02:58.340
Let's shift that to 32 points.

00:02:58.340 --> 00:03:04.390
Let's move our text according to the baseline lines over here, grid over here.

00:03:04.390 --> 00:03:06.510
This is how it looks.

00:03:06.510 --> 00:03:08.220
Let's move the Thursday.

00:03:08.220 --> 00:03:11.470
Thursday size is 18.

00:03:14.420 --> 00:03:17.475
Now here we have the problem.

00:03:17.475 --> 00:03:22.925
We need another scale which shows our small text too.

00:03:22.925 --> 00:03:28.715
We are going to use modular scale and 20 pixels and 1.3.

00:03:28.715 --> 00:03:30.440
This is already I have saved,

00:03:30.440 --> 00:03:33.020
so enter 20 pixels, 1.3 ratio.

00:03:33.020 --> 00:03:38.300
I am going to see the size smaller than this 20 pixels, it is 15.

00:03:38.300 --> 00:03:41.480
If you want, you can use 15 over here like this,

00:03:41.480 --> 00:03:47.855
15 points and move it above and below this heading.

00:03:47.855 --> 00:03:51.650
Now, why I use this one?

00:03:51.650 --> 00:03:55.760
Because this grid level doesn't show me the size for the small text.

00:03:55.760 --> 00:03:58.130
If you go to this code,

00:03:58.130 --> 00:04:01.100
you cannot see any small text over here.

00:04:01.100 --> 00:04:06.515
Heading five is 20 pixels and no size is below 20 pixels.

00:04:06.515 --> 00:04:10.130
We need a size which is below 20 pixels,

00:04:10.130 --> 00:04:12.740
so I shift it to this modular scale.

00:04:12.740 --> 00:04:15.390
Now if you see our font sizes is 20,

00:04:15.390 --> 00:04:18.350
26, 34, and 44.

00:04:18.350 --> 00:04:19.760
Same is over here.

00:04:19.760 --> 00:04:22.820
You can see heading one is 44 pixels.

00:04:22.820 --> 00:04:25.150
You can see over here font size 44 pixels,

00:04:25.150 --> 00:04:27.365
then we have 34,

00:04:27.365 --> 00:04:29.700
then we have 26, and 20.

00:04:29.700 --> 00:04:31.140
Scale is the same,

00:04:31.140 --> 00:04:36.590
just we don't have the small size calculation over here.

00:04:36.590 --> 00:04:41.790
Our next step will be to size this heading perfectly.

00:04:41.790 --> 00:04:45.830
We are going to use maybe 57 or 44.

00:04:45.830 --> 00:04:48.350
You can decide whatever you want to use.

00:04:48.350 --> 00:04:50.830
I will go with this 44 pixels.

00:04:50.830 --> 00:04:56.960
Now I'm going to select this heading and let's set it to 44 pixels.

00:04:56.960 --> 00:05:00.550
This is how it's looking right now.

00:05:00.550 --> 00:05:06.890
Let's add few more text to it so it fits on two lines.

00:05:06.890 --> 00:05:12.575
We do not want to leave a second one or two letters at the end.

00:05:12.575 --> 00:05:17.680
It is not a very good typography practice.

00:05:17.780 --> 00:05:22.840
Size is 44. Now I am going to set the line height to 44

00:05:22.840 --> 00:05:27.350
too because I want just one equal to line height, one for headings.

