00:08:01.495 --> 00:08:04.380
Now the second step.

00:08:04.380 --> 00:08:07.580
Second step is that if you see closely

00:08:07.580 --> 00:08:10.820
between these two paragraph and the lower paragraphs,

00:08:10.820 --> 00:08:15.845
I think it's a bit bigger space between all these paragraphs.

00:08:15.845 --> 00:08:18.850
Why not make them closer?

00:08:18.850 --> 00:08:23.950
We are going to Control J in this text.

00:08:23.950 --> 00:08:25.640
This is our old text,

00:08:25.640 --> 00:08:29.360
so I'm going to duplicate this layer.

00:08:29.360 --> 00:08:36.270
What we are going to do is we are going to remove one space or return over here.

00:08:36.270 --> 00:08:38.855
I pressed Enter or return over here.

00:08:38.855 --> 00:08:41.260
Now they are lined up.

00:08:41.260 --> 00:08:47.600
Now select the first line and see what's the line height is it's 32.

00:08:47.600 --> 00:08:50.825
We need something between 48 or 64.

00:08:50.825 --> 00:08:52.550
The next step is 64,

00:08:52.550 --> 00:08:56.780
but we will divide our baseline to half,

00:08:56.780 --> 00:08:59.800
so half the baseline is 16 points.

00:08:59.800 --> 00:09:04.255
I'm adding 32 plus 16, so it's 48.

00:09:04.255 --> 00:09:09.740
I'm going to shift this to 48 rather than 64,

00:09:09.740 --> 00:09:11.735
which was the previous setting.

00:09:11.735 --> 00:09:14.650
Also this one to 48.

00:09:14.650 --> 00:09:18.690
I will show you the difference once it is finished.

00:09:18.690 --> 00:09:23.070
Let me enable the pattern overlay for our baseline grid.

00:09:23.070 --> 00:09:24.500
This is our baseline grid.

00:09:24.500 --> 00:09:32.000
You can see over here that our baseline is getting off beat like in music,

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:40.200
but as soon as it goes to the next point it is again inside the pattern.

00:09:40.200 --> 00:09:44.400
It is again lined up to our baseline grid.

00:09:44.400 --> 00:09:51.550
Why? Because our baseline scale which is 48 points is basically, what's it is?

00:09:51.550 --> 00:09:58.200
It's basically 1.5 times our baseline size, so 32.

00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:01.320
Let's tell you the secret over here,

00:10:01.320 --> 00:10:04.140
32 multiplied by 1.5, 48.

00:10:04.140 --> 00:10:09.480
Whenever you try to go off beat just go something like this,

00:10:09.480 --> 00:10:14.640
multiply it with 1.5 or 1.25,

00:10:14.640 --> 00:10:18.190
32 multiply by 1.25, something like this.

00:10:19.240 --> 00:10:25.955
1.25 and 40, it might also go well,

00:10:25.955 --> 00:10:28.835
but I think 1.5 is good enough.

00:10:28.835 --> 00:10:37.135
This is how we used our baseline grid and this is the previous text.

00:10:37.135 --> 00:10:41.195
This one is previous and this one is a bit shifted up.

00:10:41.195 --> 00:10:47.855
Over here you can see a bit less gap between paragraphs and it is looking very nice.

00:10:47.855 --> 00:10:54.330
